            Return args["--text"] is equal to "hello"
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Note: Helper Functions for Tests
Process called "string_from_integer" that takes num as Integer returns String:
    Note: Convert integer to string
    If num is equal to 0:
        Return "0"
    If num is equal to 1:
        Return "1"
    If num is equal to 2:
        Return "2"
    If num is equal to 3:
        Return "3"
    If num is equal to 4:
        Return "4"
    If num is equal to 5:
        Return "5"
    If num is equal to 6:
        Return "6"
    If num is equal to 7:
        Return "7"
    If num is equal to 8:
        Return "8"
    If num is equal to 9:
        Return "9"
    If num is equal to 10:
        Return "10"
    Otherwise:
        Return "N" 